      "role": "user",
      "content": "Thanks for the suggestions. I tried a log transformation on the dependent variable, but it didn't seem to fix the skew as much as I hoped, and I'm still seeing these massive spikes in the residual plots at the higher end of the price range. If I can't get the residuals to look normal through transformations, should I just switch to a non-parametric approach or something like a Generalized Linear Model (GLM)?",
