      "content": "That makes sense. I'll look into the Gamma distribution. One more thing, though—even with the GLM, I'm worried about how these specific extreme outliers are going to affect my coefficient estimates. They seem almost intentional, like they're pulling the line away from the rest of the data. Is there a specific way to mathematically identify if these points are actually \"erroneous\" versus just being naturally extreme parts of the distribution?",
