      "content": "To mathematically distinguish between genuinely extreme but valid data points and outright errors, you should analyze leverage and influence. High leverage points are those with unusual predictor values, while influential points are those that significantly change the regression coefficients when included or excluded. Cook's Distance is a standard metric to quantitatively assess the influence of individual observations on your GLM coefficients.",
